  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7015 sitting right between the massive +19.9B gamma wall at 7025 and the +16.6B wall at 7000, dealers are in heavy selling mode to hedge their long gamma positions as spot pushes into this dense resistance zone. The PIN regime combined with this concentrated positive gamma structure creates a powerful magnet effect, with dealers expected to aggressively sell any further push toward 7025-7030 and provide buying support on any pullback toward 7000. Key inflection points are the 7025 max gamma strike above and the 6859 flip level below, where dealer behavior would shift from stabilizing to amplifying moves.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to get pinned between 7000-7025 with limited upside as dealers sell strength.",
